   Tracking the Rise of ISIS

   Middle East Forum Shillman-Ginsburg Fellow Aymenn Jawad Al-Tamimi has
   been closely tracking the rise of the Islamic State (ISIS) for two
   years. Much of what the outside world knows about the mysterious
   contagion enveloping much of Iraq and Syria can be traced to his
   pioneering work.
   For some of Jawad Al-Tamimi's more accessible writings, see the sidebar
   to the right. For more highly detailed research and translations of
   Arabic source materials related to ISIS, visit his [94]web site.
