   The Middle East Forum, a Philadelphia-based think tank, works to define
   and promote American interests in the Middle East and protect Western
   values from Middle Eastern threats. It does this in three main ways:
     * Intellectually: Through the [105]Middle East Quarterly, [106]staff
       writings, [107]lectures and [108]conference calls, the Forum
       provides context, insights, and policy recommendations.
     * Operationally: The Forum exerts an active influence through its
       projects, including [109]Campus Watch, [110]Islamist Watch, the
       [111]Legal Project, the [112]Washington Project, and the
       Shillman/Ginsburg Writing Fellowship Program.
     * Philanthropically: The Forum distributes nearly $1.5 million
       annually through its [113]Education Fund, helping researchers,
       writers, investigators, and activists around the world.

